		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Wiener filter</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>In <a href="/wiki/Signal_processing" title="Signal processing">signal processing</a>, the <b>Wiener filter</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Filter_(signal_processing)" title="Filter (signal processing)" class="mw-redirect">filter</a> proposed by <a href="/wiki/Norbert_Wiener" title="Norbert Wiener">Norbert Wiener</a> during the 1940s and published in 1949.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Its purpose is to reduce the amount of <a href="/wiki/Noise" title="Noise">noise</a> present in a signal by comparison with an estimation of the desired noiseless signal.</p>
